  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "systemd security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for systemd is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "systemd is a system and service manager that runs as PID 1 and starts the rest of the system.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nIn udev in systemd before 260, local root execution can occur via malicious hardware devices and unsanitized kernel output.(CVE-2026-40225)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for systemd is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "systemd",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
